{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The generated function signature matches the expected interface (parameter names, types, return type) specified in the description.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"CANDIDATE-TEST-CHECK: Integration test with a stubbed model can catch parser/validator wiring bugs, but misses real signature mistakes made by the live model. Agentic test (real LLM call + signature assertion) catches both wrapper issues and model-output mismatch. MOCK-MISS/LLM-DEP: correctness depends on what the real model generates from NL spec. REJECTION-GATE: Workflow rejected because behavior text is a single generation quality check, not a required multi-agentic chain.","test_description":"Run real LLM generation for a set of interface-constrained prompts, parse produced signature, and assert exact match on parameter names/types/return type against expected interface contract.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.68,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Orchestration executes attempts in order and returns immediately on the first passing attempt.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"CANDIDATE-TEST-CHECK: Unit test of loop helper catches local branching bugs but can miss module handoff errors (generator/test-runner/bookkeeping adapters). Integration test with deterministic fakes catches ordering, attempt indexing, and early-stop across boundaries. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) no required real OS/network/subprocess in behavior text, (b) no dependence on model output quality, (c) no required multi-agentic quality chain, (d) LLM decisions are not under test.","test_description":"Wire orchestrator with in-process fake generator and fake test executor that fail then pass; assert calls are in strict attempt order and no further generation/execution happens after first pass.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabi