low":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The next live attempt changes implementation content in response to prior failure context rather than resubmitting the same code.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"CANDIDATE-TEST-CHECK: Agentic one-call-with-context test can show model can vary output, but misses whether the real loop carries failure context from prior attempt correctly. Workflow test with two live attempts catches both context handoff and model behavioral response. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: behavior explicitly depends on prior-attempt context affecting next live generation.","test_description":"Execute live attempt 1 and force/observe failure context, then run live attempt 2 through real refinement path; assert attempt-2 code differs materially from attempt-1 and reflects failure-driven changes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.32,"Workflow":0.6}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The service stops after 3 failed attempts and returns a structured error with all three attempts and their test results.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"CANDIDATE-TEST-CHECK: Unit test of retry counter catches off-by-one logic but misses serialization/aggregation issues across orchestrator and result models. Integration test with deterministic always-fail stubs catches stop condition plus full error payload assembly. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) no required real OS/network/subprocess, (b) no model-output-quality dependence, (c) no multi-agentic correctness requirement.","test_description":"Wire orchestrator with deterministic failing generator/test executor for all attempts; assert exactly 3 attempts run and returned error object contains attempt metadata and per-attempt test outcomes for all three.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":7,"d